<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Tech News - Latest Headlines</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        
        body {
            font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
            background: #f5f5f5;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        
        .main-article {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: #fff;
            padding: 40px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        
        .main-article h1 {
            font-size: 32px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1a1a1a;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            line-height: 1.3;
        }
        
        .main-article p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.8;
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        
        .inline-ad {
            float: right;
            width: 300px;
            height: 250px;
            background: #e0e0e0;
            margin: 10px 0 15px 20px;
            padding: 15px;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #666;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
        
        .inline-ad::before {
            content: 'Advertisement';
            display: block;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #999;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            font-size: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }
        
        .inline-ad.sponsored {
            float: left;
            width: 300px;
            height: 250px;
            margin: 10px 20px 15px 0;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f5f5f5 0%, #e0e0e0 100%);
        }
        
        .main-article a {
            color: #0066cc;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 500;
        }
        
        .main-article a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        
        .read-more-link {
            color: #d32f2f !important;
            font-weight: 600 !important;
            margin-left: 5px;
        }
        
        .article-meta {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 13px;
            color: #666;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding-bottom: 15px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
        }
        
        .article-source {
            color: #0066cc;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        
        .ad-banner {
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 12px;
        }
        
        .newsletter-box {
            background: #f0f8ff;
            border: 2px solid #0066cc;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 30px 0;
            text-align: center;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        
        .newsletter-box h3 {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            font-family: Georgia, serif;
        }
        
        .newsletter-box input {
            padding: 10px;
            width: 250px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        
        .newsletter-box button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background: #0066cc;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        
        .sidebar-ads {
            display: none;
        }
        
        @media (min-width: 1000px) {
            .main-article {
                max-width: 700px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <article class="main-article">
        <div class="article-meta">
            <span class="article-source">TechDaily</span> | 
            <span>March 10, 2026</span> | 
            <span>By Sarah Johnson</span>
        </div>
        
        <h1>Revolutionary AI System Achieves Breakthrough in Medical Diagnosis</h1>
        
        <p>Scientists at the Artificial Intelligence Research Institute have unveiled a new system capable of detecting early-stage cancer with 99.7% accuracy, potentially revolutionizing how doctors approach diagnostic medicine. <aside class="inline-ad">Advertisement: Sign up for our newsletter to get the latest tech news delivered to your inbox!</aside> The system uses deep learning algorithms trained on millions of medical images.</p>
        
        <p>Dr. Sarah Mitchell, lead researcher on the project, explained that the AI was trained using a diverse dataset spanning multiple hospitals and patient populations. "What makes this system unique is its ability to generalize across different demographics <a href="/read-more/ai-breakthrough">Read More...</a> rather than being limited to specific patient groups," she said during a press conference.</p>
        
        <p>The technology has already undergone clinical trials at three major medical centers, with results published in the Journal of Medical AI. <aside class="inline-ad sponsored">Sponsored: Learn about our premium membership plans for healthcare professionals.</aside> Early detection has long been considered the key to successful cancer treatment, and this development could save millions of lives worldwide.</p>
        
        <p>Medical professionals have expressed cautious optimism about the findings, noting that while the results are promising, additional validation is needed before widespread adoption. <a href="/read-more/medical-ai-adoption">Read More about adoption challenges...</a> The FDA is currently reviewing the system for approval.</p>
        
        <p>Investment in AI healthcare applications has surged over the past year, with venture capital firms pouring over $15 billion into the sector. Industry analysts predict that AI-assisted diagnostics could become standard practice within the next decade.</p>
        
        <div class="newsletter-box">
            <h3>Stay Informed</h3>
            <p>Get the latest tech news delivered to your inbox</p>
            <input type="email" placeholder="Enter your email">
            <button>Subscribe</button>
        </div>
    </article>
</body>
</html>
